Specimen for @googledesign showcasing Roboto Serif by @greggazdowicz @commercialtype, a typeface designed to maximize a comfortable reading experience. Written by @sedjargon, this specimen is a reader full of tips for reading comfortably, with illustrations by @kyleplatts. ❤️❤️❤️ This was a project started pre pandemic (with @damiencorrell @bravabravo @_bird_up @likeyoucare_ @davelab6) and completed quite a bit later (with @davelab6 @tobestobs and SeHee Lee) — happy to have finally put it out into the world late last year! Shout out to @loveartprintbooks books who did months of testing to try to get us a good matte purple foil print on a flock cover (I really wanted the specimen to be soft and comfy) but alas we had to abandon ship after the foil we liked was discontinued 💀. Also to @eliserigollet who was involved in the specimen’s early days. 💘 Also note the orange diecut pages — these highlight little interstitial moments of reading-related quotes, poems, and other literary excerpts and I think they are hella cute. 💅 Trying to sneak this idea into a lot more projects 😈😈😈. #robotoserif

A lovely little book for @sarahirvinart published last year showcasing her series Rocking Chair Drawings, for which graphite was hung from the underside of a glider rocking chair to create marks on paper attached to its stationary base. The resulting drawings record the act of caring for Sarah’s daughter—from her birth on October 2, 2014, until her first birthday. We selected this narrow “hotdog”-shaped format to allow each work to be taken in individually. The folios mark the range of time in which each drawing was made, with its start date on the lefthand page and end date on the right. These simple choices create a quiet rhythm not unlike rocking a baby. Printed by @kopaprinting, set in Virgo DA from @sharp_type.

💀 FREEBIE 💀 I made a tiny zine of reviews of Home Depot’s 5 ft. Posable Skeleton with LED Eyes and *spoiler alert* the masses agree that these guys SLAP. Not to be confused with the Home Depot 12 ft. skeleton, we humble appreciators of this decoration aren't show-offs we just enjoy driving human-sized bones around in motorcycle side cars or dressing them in size 4 women's capri pants. NORMAL STUFF. Anyway, I love them sm and last week I risographed these zines with the help of @thepatienceofstone at @conveyorstudio. I'm just giving them away and I have a few left so if you want one DM me your address. I hope it will reach you by Halloween, but if not don't even worry about it because these guys are always relevant.

location.city_name: Mattress Factory - Museum of Contemporary Art

social_posts.post_text: New identity for Mattress Factory, an artist-centered museum, international residency program and renowned producer and presenter of installation art since 1977. In our work, we reimagined the Museum’s monogram, creating space for myriad interpretations: it can be read as letterforms, floor plans, a factory building and even references specific architectural details of the institution — all speaking to the challenging, site-specific artwork championed by the Museum. This monogram can also house text and imagery, further telling the story of the Museum’s centering of artists in all that they do. The identity was developed with @whoremone (❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️) and the monogram with @polytypefoundry (🥰🥰🥰). Much love to @doresick (who has trusted me now with not one but two institutional makeovers) and to the rest of Team Rebrand at @mattressfactory: Mallory Locante, @murrp and @dannyjbracken. Initiated last fall, this work extends to all facets of the museum, and will gradually be rolling out over the coming months. Stay tuned!
